description.p:
According to a first embodiment of the method, corresponding to an in-mold coating method:
the coating 10 transparent to visible light is applied in a mold, preferably by spraying. Thus, the bottom of the mold cavity is lined with material intended to form the coating 10;
the wall 8 transparent to visible light is molded on the coating, for example by injection in the context of the use of a thermoplastic material;
the wall 8 transparent to visible light is encapsulated in a sealed manner between the coating 10 transparent to visible light and the main body 6 of the bodywork panel.
